summary: The customer wants to complain about a cheesecake they bought because it is not tasting good and is melting fast. The customer wants to know if they will get a refund for the product. The customer is then asked to provide their personal details like address, ID, email etc so that the customer service can take appropriate action and let the customer know via mail.
speaker_a_summary: Emma and Rombo have a problematic pack of biscuits. They describe the packaging and the taste, and they will not buy it again. They discuss other options of biscuits to buy and eat. Rombo gives feedback on the product and wants to inform the company, Priya Ser, via email. The pack of biscuits was bought in Nagari, in the Chittoor district of Andhra Pradesh.
speaker_b_summary: A customer calls ITC to complain about poor taste and issues with a chocolate cream biscuit packet she bought. The customer support representative takes the complaint and collects information about the issue, including the location, package weight, and batch code of the product, and promises to look into the issue and work on improving the biscuit quality in the future.
cohere_points:
- A customer is calling about a cheesecake packet they bought that is of low quality
- The customer support asks them for the packet details and takes note of the issue 
- They will look into the issue and provide a solution soon 

</br>

- Address, email and batch code are collected to identify the customer 
- The packet they bought is not up to market quality standards 
- The customer support will take immediate action on the issue
